We opted for the Christmas Nine Course Menu and I have to say I was very impressed. We started with a winter melon soup (just like my grandma used to make), chicken salad, orange chicken, whole deep fried fish, barbeque ribs, lotus root and sauteed vegetables, roast duck, mochi rice (Jung), and a sweet cold azuku bean mochi soup. Everything tasted delicious, except maybe the azuki bean dessert, I would have preferred the almond float.  A few dishes were traditional, soup, duck, jung, orange chicken, but some were improved with the smallest  details like in the sauce for the fried fish there were pine nuts, and little bits of something, not sure what it was but added nicely to the flavor. The lotus root veggies had tiny bits if water chestnuts and small black beans that added just enough color and texture, it was my favorite dish. The menu was a bit pricey at about $35 pp + tax and 18% gratuity but it was very tasty and we were pretty full.  The service was fine, they were busy, and we were thankful to have a nice lunch together on Christmas day. Two thumbs up. I'm sure I'll be back for more.
